[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]I walk regularly in the Peak District, and have often had my walk disturbed by all-terrain vehicles of various sorts; 4-wheel drive cars, trail bikes, 
[normal]quad
[normal] bikes.
[normal]c)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The worst aspect of all-terrain vehicles is the way they spoil the surface of the path badly making walking and cycling very difficult if not impossible in some parts of the Peak District.
[normal]d)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Even where there are barriers to prevent entry to paths by off-
[normal]roading
[normal] vehicles these can often be got round – trail bikes and quad bikes can quite easily go through the normal barriers for cyclists; on Sunday 25
[normal]th
[normal] August 2013 while carrying out our regular 
[normal]Sustrans
[normal] route litter-pick and general check, 2 quads and a trail bike roared through 
[normal]Beeley
[normal] Woods between 
[normal]Claywheels
[normal] Lane and 
[normal]Oughtibridge
[normal] in Sheffield so we reported this on 101 (incident number 511).
[normal]e)
